in the UI directory, create a PSWEEP.FIL containing the lines

    exclude DOS\UILIBMW.LIB
    exclude DOS\UILIBLW.LIB
    exclude OS2\UILIBSW.LIB
    exclude OS2\UILIBLW.LIB
    exclude OS2\UILIBMW.LIB
    exclude QNX\UILIBMW.LIB
    exclude WIN\UILIBMW.LIB

In the Build root create the following directories

    bdiff          bin            binp           c              chkmouse
    clib           cmdedit        codegen        emu            emu86
    f77            graphlib       h              hlp            install
    misc           nlm            qh             src            techinfo
    ui             uiforms        watcom         wbed           wdisasm
    wfl            win            win386         windows        wl
    wlib           wmake          womp           wpack          wprof
    wsample        wstrip         wstub          wtouch         wv
    xmem           qnx

Create a \TMP directory on every drive

An example autoexec:

    set watcom=c:\lang
    set home=c:
    set glob=c:\etc\glob.exe
    set help=c:\etc
    set ROOTDIR=c:\
    set TMPDIR=j:\
    set ramd=j
    set ramdisk=j:
    set devdir=g:\bld
    set devdr=g
    set BLDDR=g:
    set TOOLDR=c:
    set relroot=e:
    set qnx_key=wcc
    set testmode=

an example WPROJ.RC

    e:\pat              x:\groupdir\cproj\patch
    e:\distrib          x:\groupdir\cproj\distrib
    c:\plum             x:\groupdir\cproj\plum
    c:\tools            x:\groupdir\cproj\build
    c:\lang             r:\lang
    g:\bld\windows      x:\groupdir\cproj\windows
    g:\bld\wstub        x:\groupdir\cproj\wstub
    g:\bld\c            x:\groupdir\cproj\c
    g:\bld\chkmouse     x:\groupdir\cproj\chkmouse
    g:\bld\clib         x:\groupdir\cproj\clib
